page.title: 07Ecology, Contd.
page.content: Tree creepers and Gold crests abound and almost ever house in Falkenham has it's House Martins. Pheasants are bread at nearby Kirton Lodge and at Capel hall farm. There are English and French partridge but the former are in decline. The fish in King's Fleet consist of Rudd, Roach, Perch, Tench, Pike, Carp and Eels. The small areas of woodland are mainly deciduous.Dutch Elm disease has taken its toll of mature Elm trees but many have young shoots sprouting from the base. Some rare specimens of Black Willow are being matured by residents in Falkenham. There are Tree Preservation Orders on the Cedar of labanon in front of Falkenham Hall and also on a group of trees in the garden of the Old Vicarage at Falkenham
